#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc58:0.5"
msgid "58. Dubbaṇṇakaraṇasikkhāpada"
msgstr ""
"<hgroup><h1 id=\"Bu-Pc.58\">Monks’ Confession 58: the training rule on "
"making stains</h1></hgroup>"

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1, pts-vp-pli4.120
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc58:1.1"
msgid ""
"Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa "
"ārāme."
msgstr ""
"<h2 id=\"nidana\">Origin story</h2>\n"
"<p><a class=\"pts-vp-pi\" id=\"Vin.4.120\">Vin.4.120</a><a class=\"pts-cs\" "
"id=\"Bu-Pc.58.1\">Bu-Pc.58.1</a><a class=\"pts-vp-en\" id=\"BD.2.406\""
">BD.2.406</a><a class=\"wt-pa\">1119</a>At one time the Buddha was staying "
"at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery."

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc58:1.2"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena sambahulā bhikkhū ca paribbājakā ca sāketā sāvatthiṃ "
"addhānamaggappaṭipannā honti."
msgstr ""
"At that time a number of monks and wanderers were robbed by thieves while "
"traveling on the main road from Sāketa to Sāvatthī."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc58:1.3"
msgid "Antarāmagge corā nikkhamitvā te acchindiṃsu."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc58:1.4"
msgid ""
"Sāvatthiyā rājabhaṭā nikkhamitvā te core sabhaṇḍe gahetvā bhikkhūnaṃ santike "
"dūtaṃ pāhesuṃ—"
msgstr ""
"The King’s men set out from Sāvatthī and caught the thieves and their loot. "
"They then sent a message to the monks:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc58:1.5"
msgid "“āgacchantu, bhadantā, sakaṃ sakaṃ cīvaraṃ sañjānitvā gaṇhantū”ti."
msgstr "“Venerables, please come and pick out your own robes.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc58:1.6"
msgid "Bhikkhū na sañjānanti."
msgstr "But the monks did not recognize them."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc58:1.7"
msgid "Te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "The people complained and criticized them,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc58:1.8"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma bhadantā attano attano cīvaraṃ na sañjānissantī”ti."
msgstr "“How can they not recognize their own robes?”</p>"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc58:1.9"
msgid ""
"Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tesaṃ manussānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ."
msgstr ""
"<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1120</a>The monks heard the complaints of those people,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc58:1.10"
msgid "Atha kho te bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ."
msgstr "and they told the Master."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc58:1.11"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe bhikkhusaṃghaṃ "
"sannipātāpetvā bhikkhūnaṃ tadanucchavikaṃ tadanulomikaṃ dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā "
"bhikkhū āmantesi—"
msgstr ""
"He had the Order of monks assembled, gave a teaching on what is right and "
"seemly, and then addressed the monks,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc58:1.12"
msgid ""
"“tena hi, bhikkhave, bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññapessāmi dasa atthavase "
"paṭicca—"
msgstr ""
"“Well then, monks, I will lay down a training rule for the following ten "
"reasons:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc58:1.13"
msgid "saṃghasuṭṭhutāya, saṃghaphāsutāya … pe …"
msgstr ""
"for the well-being of the Order, for the comfort of the Order, for the "
"restraint of bad people, for the ease of well-behaved monks, for the "
"restraint of corruptions in the present life, for avoiding corruptions in "
"future lives, to give rise to confidence in those without it, to increase "
"the confidence of those who have it,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc58:1.14"
msgid "saddhammaṭṭhitiyā, vinayānuggahāya."
msgstr ""
"for the continuation of the true Teaching, and for supporting the training."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc58:1.15"
msgid "Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:</p>"

#. HTML: </p><p><b class="rule">
#. REF: sc3
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc58:1.16"
msgid ""
"“Navaṃ pana bhikkhunā cīvaralābhena tiṇṇaṃ dubbaṇṇakaraṇānaṃ aññataraṃ "
"dubbaṇṇakaraṇaṃ ādātabbaṃ—nīlaṃ vā kaddamaṃ vā kāḷasāmaṃ vā. Anādā ce "
"bhikkhu tiṇṇaṃ dubbaṇṇakaraṇānaṃ aññataraṃ dubbaṇṇakaraṇaṃ navaṃ cīvaraṃ "
"paribhuñjeyya, pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr ""
"<h2 id=\"pannatti\">Final ruling</h2>\n"
"<p class=\"rule\"><a class=\"wt-pa\">1121</a>‘When a monk obtains a new "
"robe, <a class=\"pts-vp-en\" id=\"BD.2.407\">BD.2.407</a> he should apply "
"one of three kinds of stain: blue-green, mud-color, or dark brown. If a monk "
"uses a new robe without applying any of the three kinds of stain, he commits "
"an offense entailing confession.’”</p>"

#. HTML: </b></p><p><b class="term">
#. REF: sc4
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc58:2.1.1"
msgid "Navaṃ nāma"
msgstr ""
"<h2 id=\"pada\">Definitions</h2>\n"
"<p><a class=\"pts-cs\" id=\"Bu-Pc.58.2\"></a><a class=\"pts-cs\" id=\"Bu-"
"Pc.58.2.1\">Bu-Pc.58.2.1</a><a class=\"wt-pa\">1122</a><term>New</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc58:2.1.2"
msgid "akatakappaṃ vuccati."
msgstr "<gloss>a mark has not been made is what is meant.</gloss></p>"

#. HTML: </b></p><p><b class="term">
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc58:2.1.3"
msgid "Cīvaraṃ nāma"
msgstr "<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1123</a><term>A robe</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc58:2.1.4"
msgid "channaṃ cīvarānaṃ aññataraṃ cīvaraṃ."
msgstr ""
"<gloss>one of the six kinds of robe.<span class=\"note\" hidden>The six are "
"linen, cotton, silk, wool, sunn hemp, and hemp; see <span class=\"ref\""
">MS.3.1595</span>.</span></gloss></p>"

#. HTML: </b></p><p><b class="term">
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc58:2.1.5"
msgid "Tiṇṇaṃ dubbaṇṇakaraṇānaṃ aññataraṃ dubbaṇṇakaraṇaṃ ādātabbanti"
msgstr ""
"<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1124</a><term>He should apply one of three kinds of "
"stain</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc58:2.1.6"
msgid "antamaso kusaggenapi ādātabbaṃ."
msgstr ""
"<gloss>even if he just applies the amount on the tip of a blade of "
"grass.</gloss></p>"

#. HTML: </b></p><p><b class="term">
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc58:2.1.7"
msgid "Nīlaṃ nāma"
msgstr "<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1125</a><term>Blue-green</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc58:2.1.8"
msgid "dve nīlāni—"
msgstr ""
"<gloss>there are two kinds of <a class=\"pts-vp-en\" id=\"BD.2.408\""
">BD.2.408</a> blue-green:"

#. HTML: </b>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc58:2.1.9"
msgid "kaṃsanīlaṃ, palāsanīlaṃ."
msgstr "the color of copper-sulphate and the color of leaves.</gloss></p>"

#. HTML: </p><p><b class="term">
#. REF: sc8
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc58:2.1.10"
msgid "Kaddamo nāma"
msgstr "<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1126</a><term>Mud-color</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc58:2.1.11"
msgid "odako vuccati."
msgstr ""
"<gloss>water is what is meant.<span class=\"note\" hidden>According to <span "
"class=\"ref\">Vin-vn-ṭ.1626</span> (presumably commenting on <i lang=\"pi\""
">kaddamena</i> at <span class=\"ref\">Kkh.</span>): “With mud means: water "
"with mud, dry mud, etc., is included,” <i lang=\"pi\">kaddamenāti "
"udakānukaddamasukkhakaddamādiṃ saṅgaṇhāti</i>.</span></gloss></p>"

#. HTML: </b></p><p><b class="term">
#. REF: sc9
#. VAR: kāḷasāmakaṃ → kāḷakaṃ (bj, s1-3)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc58:2.1.12"
msgid "Kāḷasāmaṃ nāma"
msgstr "<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1127</a><term>Dark brown</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc58:2.1.13"
msgid "yaṃ kiñci kāḷasāmakaṃ."
msgstr "<gloss>whatever is dark brownish.</gloss></p>"

#. HTML: </b></p><p><b class="term">
#. REF: sc10, pts-vp-pli4.121
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc58:2.1.14"
msgid "Anādā ce bhikkhu tiṇṇaṃ dubbaṇṇakaraṇānaṃ aññataraṃ dubbaṇṇakaraṇanti"
msgstr ""
"<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1128</a><term>If a monk […] without applying any of "
"the three kinds of stain</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc58:2.1.15"
msgid ""
"antamaso kusaggenapi anādiyitvā tiṇṇaṃ dubbaṇṇakaraṇānaṃ aññataraṃ "
"dubbaṇṇakaraṇaṃ navaṃ cīvaraṃ paribhuñjati, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"<gloss>if he uses a new robe without first applying one of the three kinds "
"of stain, even if just the amount on the tip of a blade of grass, <a class"
"=\"pts-vp-pi\" id=\"Vin.4.121\">Vin.4.121</a> he commits an offense "
"entailing confession.</gloss></p>"

#. HTML: </b></p><p>
#. REF: sc11
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc58:2.2.1"
msgid "Anādinne anādinnasaññī paribhuñjati, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"<h2 id=\"cakka\">Permutations</h2>\n"
"<p><a class=\"pts-cs\" id=\"Bu-Pc.58.2.2\">Bu-Pc.58.2.2</a><a class=\"wt-pa\""
">1129</a>If it has not been applied, and he perceives that it has not, and "
"he uses the robe, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc58:2.2.2"
msgid "Anādinne vematiko paribhuñjati, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If it has not been applied, but he is unsure of it, and he uses the robe, he "
"commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc58:2.2.3"
msgid "Anādinne ādinnasaññī paribhuñjati, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If it has not been applied, but he perceives that it has, and he uses the "
"robe, he commits an offense entailing confession.</p>"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc12
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc58:2.2.4"
msgid "Ādinne anādinnasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1130</a>If it has been applied, but he perceives that "
"it has not, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc58:2.2.5"
msgid "Ādinne vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If it has been applied, but he is unsure if it has, he commits an offense of "
"wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc58:2.2.6"
msgid "Ādinne ādinnasaññī, anāpatti."
msgstr ""
"If it has been applied, and he perceives that it has, there is no "
"offense.</p>"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc13
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc58:2.3.1"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr ""
"<h2 id=\"anapatti\">Non-offenses</h2>\n"
"<p><a class=\"pts-cs\" id=\"Bu-Pc.58.2.3\">Bu-Pc.58.2.3</a><a class=\"pts-vp-"
"en\" id=\"BD.2.409\">BD.2.409</a><a class=\"wt-pa\">1131</a>There is no "
"offense:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc58:2.3.2"
msgid ""
"ādiyitvā paribhuñjati, kappo naṭṭho hoti, kappakatokāso jiṇṇo hoti, "
"kappakatena akappakataṃ saṃsibbitaṃ hoti, aggaḷe anuvāte paribhaṇḍe, "
"ummattakassa, ādikammikassāti."
msgstr ""
"if he applies the stain and then uses it; if the mark has disappeared; if "
"the area where the mark was applied is worn; if what had been marked is sewn "
"together with what has not been marked; if it is a patch; if it is any kind "
"of border;<span class=\"note\" hidden>I understand <i lang=\"pi\">anuvāta</i>"
" and <i lang=\"pi\">paribhaṇḍa</i> to refer to long borders and short "
"borders respectively.</span> if he is insane; if he is the first "
"offender.</p>"

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsutta">
#. REF: sc14
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc58:2.3.3"
msgid "Dubbaṇṇakaraṇasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ aṭṭhamaṃ."
msgstr ""
"<hr><p class=\"endsutta\"><a class=\"wt-pa\">1132</a>The eighth rule, the "
"training rule on making stains, is finished.<a class=\"pts-vp-en\" id=\"BD.2."
"410\">BD.2.410</a></p>"
